---
const stack = ["Astro", "React", "TypeScript", "Tailwind", "Vercel"];
---

<aside
  class="w-full rounded-md border border-stone-300 bg-stone-100/80 p-4 shadow-[0_1rem_3rem_rgba(28,28,28,0.08)] dark:border-stone-800 dark:bg-stone-900/80"
  aria-label="Current engineering focus"
>
  <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase text-[#C63D32] dark:text-[#C63D32]">
    Currently
  </p>
  <h2 class="mt-2 text-lg font-black leading-6 text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">
    Building useful web experiences with a practical full-stack lens.
  </h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
    I care about interfaces that feel clear, systems that stay maintainable,
    and teams that keep learning while shipping.
  </p>

  <dl class="mt-4 grid gap-3 text-sm">
    <div>
      <dt class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">Focus</dt>
      <dd class="mt-1 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
        Accessible frontend, reliable product flows, and performance-minded delivery.
      </dd>
    </div>
    <div>
      <dt class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">Recent work</dt>
      <dd class="mt-1 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
        Modernizing this portfolio to Astro 6, React 19, Tailwind 4, and Vercel previews.
      </dd>
    </div>
  </dl>

  <ul class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2" aria-label="Core stack">
    {
      stack.map((item) => (
        <li class="rounded-md border border-stone-300 px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-bold text-stone-700 dark:border-stone-700 dark:text-stone-200">
          {item}
        </li>
      ))
    }
  </ul>
</aside>
